BlackRock closed Q4 2025 with a record $14 trillion in assets under management, driven by $698 billion in full year net inflows, including $342 billion in the quarter, according to its earnings release.

The firm posted $7.01 billion in Q4 revenue and $1.13 billion in net income, as ETF demand and market gains lifted asset-based fees.

@BlackRock is already a major crypto gateway through its iShares Bitcoin Trust (IBIT), which pulled in tens of billions of dollars in 2025, embedding Bitcoin directly into global institutional portfolios.
